																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">I will plant those wastes with cedar and acacia, myrtle and olive; rear, in that desert soil, fir and elm and box besides;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">ut videant, et sciant, et recogitent, et intelligant pariter, quia manus Domini fecit hoc, et Sanctus IsraÃ«l creavit illud.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">That they may see and know, and consider, and understand together that the hand of the Lord hath done this, and the Holy One of Israel hath created it.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">proof for all to see and recognize, for all to mark and to consider, that the Lordâ€™s hand was there; who but he, the Holy One of Israel, creates?</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">Prope facite judicium vestrum, dicit Dominus; Afferte, si quid forte habetis, dicit rex Jacob.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">Bring your cause near, saith the Lord: bring hither, if you have any thing to allege, saith the King of Jacob.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">Come then, says the Lord, your pleadings! Let the King of Jacob hear your contentions;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">Accedant, et nuntient nobis quÃ¦cumque ventura sunt; priora quÃ¦ fuerunt, nuntiate, et ponemus cor nostrum, et sciemus novissima eorum; et quÃ¦ ventura sunt, indicate nobis.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">Let them come, and tell us all things that are to come: tell us the former things what they were: and we will set our heart upon them, and shall know the latter end of them, and tell us the things that are to come.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">let them come forward, these other gods, and tell us the future.  So read the past for us, that the study of it may disclose what needs must follow; coming events make known.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">Annuntiate quÃ¦ ventura sunt in futurum, et sciemus quia dii estis vos; bene quoque aut male, si potestis, facite, et loquamur et videamus simul.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">Shew the things that are to come hereafter, and we shall know that ye are gods. Do ye also good or evil, if you can: and let us speak, and see together.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">Foretell you what is yet to be, we shall know you are gods indeed. Then, if you have the power, grant good or ill fortune to mankind; confer we, and pass judgement on it!</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">Ecce vos estis ex nihilo, et opus vestrum ex eo quod non est: abominatio est qui elegit vos.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">Behold, you are of nothing, and your work of that which hath no being: he that hath chosen you is an abomination.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">Why, you are all empty air, a nothing that nothing can effect; he courts his own shame, that makes choice of you.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">Suscitavi ab aquilone, et veniet ab ortu solis: vocabit nomen meum, et adducet magistratus quasi lutum, et velut plastes conculcans humum.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">I have raised up one from the north, and he shall come from the rising of the sun: he shall call upon my name, and he shall make princes to be as dirt, and as the potter treading clay.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">I summoned one from the north country; from the east his coming should be, and ever he should invoke my name.  Princes he should harry to and fro, lightly as potter treads out his clay.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">Quis annuntiavit ab exordio ut sciamus, et a principio ut dicamus: Justus es? Non est neque annuntians, neque prÃ¦dicens, neque audiens sermones vestros.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">Who hath declared from the beginning, that we may know: and from time of old, that we may say: Thou art just. There is none that sheweth, nor that foretelleth, nor that heareth your words.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">Which of you foretold this from the first? Let us recognize it. Which of you knew it from the beginning? We must needs say, His plea is just. But no, none gave tidings of it, none foretold it; there was no word came from you.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">Primus ad Sion dicet: Ecce adsunt, et Jerusalem evangelistam dabo.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">The first shall say to Sion: Behold they are here, and to Jerusalem I will give an evangelist.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">Who will be the first  to tell Sion, Here, here they are? He shall carry my good news to Jerusalem.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">Et vidi, et non erat neque ex istis quisquam qui iniret consilium, et interrogatus responderet verbum.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">And I saw, and there was no one even among them to consult, or who, when I asked, could answer a word.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">But when I looked, there was none of them that could offer counsel, or give a word in answer when I questioned him.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Ecce omnes injusti, et vana opera eorum; ventus et inane simulacra eorum.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Behold they are all in the wrong, and their works are vain: their idols are wind and vanity.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">None of them has right on his side; all their doings are nothingness; no better than empty air the images men make of them.</div></div></td>
								</tr>					</tbody>
